<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Litia">
  <h1 class="pageTitle">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="subtle">Last updated: January 18, 2026</p>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Litia is designed to minimize data collection. The app uses the TrueDepth camera for on-device eye tracking and does not store or transmit camera images or video.
    </p>

    <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>On-device learning progress</b> (e.g., activity completion, scores) stored locally.</li>
      <li><b>Settings</b> (e.g., preferred mode) stored locally.</li>
      <li><b>No biometrics</b>: we do not store face scans, templates, or raw camera footage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Camera usage</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Used for real-time gaze interaction only.</li>
      <li>Processed on device and discarded.</li>
      <li>No camera recordings are saved or uploaded.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Children’s privacy</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not show ads or behavioral tracking.</li>
      <li>We do not sell personal data.</li>
      <li>Parents/guardians can request deletion of local data by uninstalling the app.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Email: <a href="mailto:support@litia.app">support@litia.app</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
